  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Realization of Human Security by Improving Living Conditions of Crisis Affected Communities and Building Their Resilience in Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project intends to respond to immediate humanitarian needs and improve living conditions of internally displaced persons, as well as build resilience of the crisis affected population. This project approach ensures immediate life-saving activities through humanitarian response, whilst strengthening the resilience to subsequent shocks such as floods but also recurrent drought conditions, ensuring communities are prepared to cope with shocks, thereby reducing the re-emergence of instability driving factors that can reverse the recovery progress already achieved in those regions. Through the preparedness, response and resilience angle, the project aims to contribute to linking humanitarian support to development, ensuring long-term sustainable solutions for communities at risk of natural disasters.</narrative>
  </description>
